## Section 4: Scope and Boundaries

### Allowed without asking:
- Create new files within `src/app/components/` for the feature being worked on
- Modify existing files within `src/app/components/` for the feature being worked on
- Add imports from existing shared code: `src/app/components/ui/` (shadcn), `src/app/components/countryData.ts`, `src/app/components/layerData.ts`, `src/app/components/flagComponents.tsx`
- Add imports from existing Figma components in `src/imports/`
- Create or update test files for code being changed
- Update feature documentation in `/docs/features/` to reflect changes made
- Add new static data entries to `countryData.ts` or `layerData.ts` (following existing data shape)

### STOP and ask before:
- Modifying `src/app/App.tsx` — it owns all global state and is the root of the entire app; changes here affect everything
- Modifying any file in `src/app/components/ui/` — these are shared shadcn/ui primitives used (or available) across all features
- Modifying any file in `src/imports/` — these are Figma-generated and may be overwritten by Figma Make re-exports
- Modifying `src/styles/theme.css` or `src/styles/tailwind.css` — these define the global theme and affect all components
- Modifying `src/styles/fonts.css` — font stack changes affect the entire app
- Adding, removing, or upgrading any dependency in `package.json`
- Introducing a new pattern that does not follow existing conventions (new state management approach, new CSS methodology, new export pattern)
- Creating files outside `src/app/components/` or `src/imports/`
- Modifying `vite.config.ts`, `postcss.config.mjs`, or `index.html`
- Modifying `Design.md` or `Logic.md` — these are authoritative specifications
- Deleting any file — always show the file path and ask for confirmation before removing

### NEVER do (even if asked — push back and explain why):
- Push to git, merge branches, or modify git history
- Modify `.env` files containing secrets or credentials
- Install packages from sources other than npm
- Delete or overwrite `Design.md` or `Logic.md` without explicit confirmation — these are the project's source of truth
- Add `// @ts-ignore`, `// eslint-disable`, or other suppression comments without explicit approval
- Rename or restructure Figma SVG path modules (`src/imports/svg-*.ts`) — these are auto-generated with hash-based names tied to Figma export IDs

