## Section 7: Error Handling and Recovery

- If a command fails, read the error message fully before retrying. Do NOT retry the same command without changing something.
- If an error cannot be resolved in 2 attempts, STOP. Output the error, what you tried, and ask for guidance.
- If a test fails after your change, do NOT delete or skip the test. Fix the code to pass the test. If the test itself is wrong, explain why and ask for permission to modify it.
- If a linter or type checker reports errors after your change, fix all of them before considering the task complete. Do NOT leave suppression comments (`// @ts-ignore`, `// eslint-disable`) unless explicitly approved.
- This project uses `npm install --legacy-peer-deps` due to a peer dependency conflict between `react-leaflet@5` (requires React 19) and `react@18.3.1`. Always use `--legacy-peer-deps` when installing dependencies.
- The dev server runs via `npm run dev` (Vite). Default port is 5173 but may increment if ports are occupied.
- There is no TypeScript compiler config (`tsconfig.json`). Type checking is done by the IDE, not a build step. Be extra careful with types — there is no CI gate.

